Prevention Checklist: Stay Safe from Cyberbullying

.Keep your social media accounts private and only accept requests from people you know.
.Avoid sharing personal information like phone number, address, or daily routine online.
.Think before posting—once something is online, it can be misused or reshared.
.Do not respond to abusive messages instead block and report the account.
.Save evidence (screenshots, chat logs) in case you need to file a complaint.
.Talk to someone you trust friends, family, or teachers if you feel uncomfortable.
.Use platform tools like report, mute, and restrict to control interactions.
.Be respectful online, do not engage in trolling or spreading rumors about others.

Financial / UPI Safety Tips:

.Never share your UPI PIN, OTP, or banking details with anyone even if they claim to be from a bank.
.Do not click on suspicious links claiming prizes, refunds, or urgent payments.

